metadata.name: Bal du Moulin de la Galette #1/5
metadata.description: "Bal du Moulin de la Galette" (Dancing at the Moulin de la Galette) is one of the most famous works of Pierre-Auguste Renoir's Impressionism movement. The painting was painted in 1876 and depicts a Sunday ball held at an entertainment venue called the Moulin de la Galette in the famous Montmartre district of Paris.
